1.

{
  __schema {
    queryType { name }
    mutationType { name }
    subscriptionType { name }
    types {
      name
      kind
      description
      fields {
        name
        description
        type {
          name
          kind
        }
      }
    }
  }
}


2.

{
  __schema {
    queryType { name }
    mutationType { name }
    subscriptionType { name }
  }
}

3.

3. Fetch All Query Fields

Once you know the name of the root query type (usually Query), you can expand:

{
  __type(name: "Query") {
    name
    fields {
      name
      description
      type {
        name
        kind
      }
    }
  }
}

4.

4. Describe All Scalars and Enums

To inspect available scalars and enums:

{
  __schema {
    types {
      name
      kind
      enumValues {
        name
      }
    }
  }
}
